{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775840546017,"sessionID":"ses_287a9a86fffe04a1JhL01vrlEY","part":{"id":"prt_d78572e81001c0SXL7EY9vEt3E","messageID":"msg_d7856d52a001eIHh6gOFKrvZP1","sessionID":"ses_287a9a86fffe04a1JhL01vrlEY","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:11","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Spec: AR-002 — CRD CodeInterpreter Type Definition\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-002  \n**Module:** pkg/apis  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n\nDefine the Go type definitions for the CodeInterpreter Custom Resource Definition (CRD) under the API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreter CRD Type Package Structure\n\nThe system SHALL define the CodeInterpreter CRD Go types in the package `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` following Kubernetes CRD conventions.\n\n#### Scenario: Package compiles successfully\n- **GIVEN** a clean Go module at repository root\n- **WHEN** the operator runs `go build ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...`\n- **THEN** the package SHALL compile without errors\n\n#### Scenario: Package follows project conventions\n- **GIVEN** the package `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`\n- **WHEN** inspecting package files\n- **THEN** all files SHALL have consistent package naming, proper doc.go documentation, and follow project conventions\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreter Root Type Definition\n\nThe system SHALL define a `CodeInterpreter` struct that implements the `runtime.Object` interface and includes standard Kubernetes metadata, spec, and status fields.\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter implements runtime.Object\n- **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreter` struct defined in `codeinterpreter_types.go`\n- **WHEN** the code is compiled\n- **THEN** `CodeInterpreter` SHALL implement `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object` interface\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter has correct TypeMeta\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` instance\n- **WHEN** accessing its `TypeMeta` fields\n- **THEN** `APIVersion` SHALL default to `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` and `Kind` SHALL be `CodeInterpreter`\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter has correct kubebuilder resource markers\n- **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreter` struct with kubebuilder markers\n- **WHEN** inspecting the markers\n- **THEN** it SHALL include `+kubebuilder:object:root=true`, `+kubebuilder:resource:path=codeinterpreters`, and `+kubebuilder:subresource:status`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterSpec Definition\n\nThe system SHALL define a `CodeInterpreterSpec` struct with fields for configuring code execution capabilities and runtime environment.\n\n#### Scenario: Required spec fields are present\n- **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreterSpec` struct definition\n- **WHEN** inspecting its fields\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain at minimum: `image` (string) as the container image for the interpreter, `language` (string) for supported programming language, and `runtimeClassName` (string, optional) for sandbox runtime configuration\n\n#### Scenario: Resource configuration fields are present\n- **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreterSpec` struct definition\n- **WHEN** inspecting its fields\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain `resources` (ResourceRequirements, optional) for CPU/memory limits, and `storage` (StorageSpec, optional) for persistent storage configuration\n\n#### Scenario: Security and sandbox fields are present\n- **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreterSpec` struct definition\n- **WHEN** inspecting its fields\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain `securityContext` (SecurityContext, optional) for pod-level security settings, and `networkPolicy` (NetworkPolicySpec, optional) for network isolation\n\n#### Scenario: Execution configuration fields are present\n- **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreterSpec` struct definition\n- **WHEN** inspecting its fields\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain `timeoutSeconds` (int32, optional) for execution timeout, `maxMemoryMB` (int32, optional) for memory limits, `allowedImports` ([]string, optional) for package whitelist, and `environment` ([]EnvVar, optional) for environment variables\n\n#### Scenario: JSON tags use camelCase\n- **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreterSpec` struct with field tags\n- **WHEN** serializing to JSON\n- **THEN** field names SHALL use camelCase (e.g., `runtimeClassName`, `timeoutSeconds`, `maxMemoryMB`, `allowedImports`)\n\n#### Scenario: Default values are documented\n- **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreterSpec` struct with kubebuilder markers\n- **THEN** `timeoutSeconds` SHALL have default `300`, and `maxMemoryMB` SHALL have default `512`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: ProgrammingLanguage Type Definition\n\nThe system SHALL define a `ProgrammingLanguage` type with supported language enumeration and validation.\n\n#### Scenario: ProgrammingLanguage enum is defined\n- **GIVEN** the `ProgrammingLanguage` type definition\n- **WHEN** inspecting the type\n- **THEN** it SHALL be a string type with kubebuilder validation enum containing: `python`, `javascript`, `typescript`, `go`, `rust`, `java`, `cpp`\n\n#### Scenario: Language validation passes for valid values\n- **GIVEN** the `ProgrammingLanguage` type with validation\n- **WHEN** validating with `language: python`\n- **THEN** it SHALL pass validation\n\n#### Scenario: Language validation fails for invalid values\n- **GIVEN** the `ProgrammingLanguage` type with validation\n- **WHEN** validating with `language: invalid`\n- **THEN** it SHALL fail validation with an appropriate error\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterStorageSpec Definition\n\nThe system SHALL define a `CodeInterpreterStorageSpec` struct for configuring persistent storage.\n\n#### Scenario: Storage spec has required fields\n- **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreterStorageSpec` struct definition\n- **WHEN** inspecting its fields\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain `size` (Quantity, required), `storageClassName` (string, optional), and `accessMode` (string, optional with default `ReadWriteOnce`)\n\n#### Scenario: Access mode validation\n- **GIVEN** the storage spec with kubebuilder markers\n- **WHEN** validating with `accessMode: ReadWriteMany`\n- **THEN** it SHALL pass validation (allowed values: ReadWriteOnce, ReadOnlyMany, ReadWriteMany)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterStatus Definition\n\nThe system SHALL define a `CodeInterpreterStatus` struct with conditions, phase, and observed state fields.\n\n#### Scenario: Status has conditions\n- **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreterStatus` struct definition\n- **WHEN** inspecting its fields\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain a `conditions` field of type `[]metav1.Condition`\n\n#### Scenario: Status has phase field\n- **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreterStatus` struct definition\n- **WHEN** inspecting its fields\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain a `phase` field of type `CodeInterpreterPhase` with enum values: `Pending`, `Provisioning`, `Ready`, `Failed`, `Terminating`\n\n#### Scenario: Status has runtime information\n- **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreterStatus` struct definition\n- **WHEN** inspecting its fields\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain `interpreterURL` (string, optional), `lastExecutionTime` (Time, optional), and `executionCount` (int64, optional)\n\n#### Scenario: Status subresource marker\n- **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreter` struct with kubebuilder markers\n- **WHEN** inspecting the markers\n- **THEN** it SHALL include `// +kubebuilder:subresource:status` marker\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterCondition Type Definition\n\nThe system SHALL define a `CodeInterpreterConditionType` type with supported condition types.\n\n#### Scenario: Condition types are defined\n- **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreterConditionType` type and constants\n- **WHEN** inspecting the constants\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain: `CodeInterpreterConditionReady`, `CodeInterpreterConditionStorageReady`, `CodeInterpreterConditionRuntimeReady`, `CodeInterpreterConditionExecutionAvailable`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterList Definition\n\nThe system SHALL define a `CodeInterpreterList` struct for list operations.\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreterList implements runtime.Object\n- **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreterList` struct defined in `codeinterpreter_types.go`\n- **WHEN** the code is compiled\n- **THEN** `CodeInterpreterList` SHALL implement `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object` interface\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreterList has items field\n- **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreterList` struct definition\n- **WHEN** inspecting its fields\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain an `items` field of type `[]CodeInterpreter` with `+kubebuilder:validation:Required` marker\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: DeepCopy Methods Generation\n\nThe system SHALL include generated DeepCopy methods for all CodeInterpreter CRD types to support Kubernetes API machinery.\n\n#### Scenario: DeepCopy methods exist\n- **GIVEN** the generated code from `controller-gen`\n- **WHEN** inspecting `zz_generated.deepcopy.go`\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain `DeepCopyInto`, `DeepCopy`, and `DeepCopyObject` methods for `CodeInterpreter`, `CodeInterpreterSpec`, `CodeInterpreterStatus`, `CodeInterpreterList`, `ProgrammingLanguage`, `CodeInterpreterStorageSpec`, and `CodeInterpreterCondition`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Scheme Registration\n\nThe system SHALL register CodeInterpreter types with the runtime scheme.\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter in scheme\n- **GIVEN** the `register.go` file in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`\n- **WHEN** inspecting the `addKnownTypes` function\n- **THEN** it SHALL register `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` types with the scheme builder alongside existing `AgentRuntime` types\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Code Generation Integration\n\nThe system SHALL integrate with `controller-gen` for generating DeepCopy methods and CRD manifests.\n\n#### Scenario: Controller-gen generates code\n- **GIVEN** the `Makefile` with `gen-crd` and `generate` targets\n- **WHEN** the operator runs `make generate`\n- **THEN** it SHALL invoke `controller-gen object` to generate DeepCopy methods including CodeInterpreter types\n\n---\n\n## File Index\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` | CodeInterpreter type definitions |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` | Scheme registration (updated to include CodeInterpreter) |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Package documentation (updated to list CodeInterpreter) |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | Generated DeepCopy methods (updated) |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `k8s.io/api/core/v1` - Kubernetes core types (ResourceRequirements, SecurityContext, EnvVar)\n- `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` - Kubernetes metadata types\n- `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime` - Runtime.Object interface\n- `sigs.k8s.io/controller-tools` (controller-gen) - Code generation\n\n---\n\n## Notes\n\n- JSON tags SHALL use camelCase per project conventions\n- Go structs SHALL use PascalCase per Go conventions\n- Kubebuilder markers SHALL follow standard Kubernetes CRD patterns\n- The CRD scope SHALL be `Namespaced` (as per deployment/design.md)\n- CodeInterpreter SHALL reuse patterns from AgentRuntime where applicable\n- REST resource plural: `codeinterpreters`\n- Short names: `ci`, `cis`\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775840545989,"end":1775840546014}}}}
