{"type":"text","timestamp":1775840563678,"sessionID":"ses_287a9a86fffe04a1JhL01vrlEY","part":{"id":"prt_d78586c0e001j4Phw8vK75WDB0","messageID":"msg_d78584d15001J4Ra806ybPvFLZ","sessionID":"ses_287a9a86fffe04a1JhL01vrlEY","type":"text","text":"Done! I've updated the `delta-spec.md` file with the AR-002 requirements for the CodeInterpreter CRD. The document now includes:\n\n**Key Requirements Defined:**\n1. **Package Structure** — CodeInterpreter types in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`\n2. **Root Type** — `CodeInterpreter` implementing `runtime.Object`\n3. **Spec Definition** — `CodeInterpreterSpec` with fields for:\n   - `image` (required)\n   - `language` (ProgrammingLanguage enum)\n   - `runtimeClassName`, `resources`, `storage`\n   - `securityContext`, `networkPolicy`\n   - `timeoutSeconds`, `maxMemoryMB`, `allowedImports`, `environment`\n4. **ProgrammingLanguage Type** — Enum with validation for: python, javascript, typescript, go, rust, java, cpp\n5. **Storage Spec** — `CodeInterpreterStorageSpec` with size, storageClassName, accessMode\n6. **Status Definition** — `CodeInterpreterStatus` with conditions, phase, interpreterURL, execution stats\n7. **Condition Types** — Ready, StorageReady, RuntimeReady, ExecutionAvailable\n8. **List Type** — `CodeInterpreterList` for collection operations\n9. **DeepCopy Generation** — All types need generated methods\n10. **Scheme Registration** — Types registered alongside AgentRuntime\n11. **Code Generation** — Integration with controller-gen\n\nEach requirement includes **GIVEN/WHEN/THEN** acceptance scenarios following the OpenSpec format. The file structure follows the same conventions as AR-001 (AgentRuntime) for consistency.","time":{"start":1775840563676,"end":1775840563676}}}
